%% Reviewed 2026-03-26 for B-001 to show Odylith bootstrap, governed-surface materialization, and the validation flow that keeps the product boundary coherent.
sequenceDiagram
    participant Repo as Product or host repo
    participant CLI as odylith CLI
    participant Profile as repo profile
    participant Context as context engine
    participant Memory as memory layer
    participant Gov as governance engine
    participant Eval as tribunal/remediator
    participant Agents as router/orchestrator
    participant Surfaces as governed surfaces
    participant Proof as validation harness

    Repo->>CLI: odylith install | odylith sync
    CLI->>Profile: resolve repo truth roots
    CLI->>Context: bootstrap grounding + retained packets
    CLI->>Memory: bootstrap Lance/Tantivy retrieval + local runtime state
    CLI->>Gov: bootstrap delivery intelligence + registry + sync
    CLI->>Eval: bootstrap dossier + packet contracts
    CLI->>Agents: bootstrap route/plan execution controls
    Gov->>Surfaces: render Radar / Atlas / Registry / Compass / Casebook / Dashboard
    Eval->>Surfaces: publish diagnosis + remediation evidence
    Agents->>Surfaces: publish routing + closeout posture
    Context->>Proof: validate packet contracts
    Memory->>Proof: validate retrieval state and memory posture
    Gov->>Proof: validate governed surface freshness and traceability
    Eval->>Proof: validate dossier and correction-packet contracts
    Agents->>Proof: validate routed execution payloads
    Proof-->>Repo: accept only if product surfaces and runtime contracts stay coherent
